parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained increase in engine revs while idling can cause the temperature gauge to rise rapidly, potentially leading to engine damage, overheating, or even engine failure.
symptoms: The engine revs intensify suddenly while idling
the revs go up and down repeatedly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked engine head can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of power, overheating, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
A failed timing belt can cause engine damage, leading to a loss of power, overheating, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
A faulty oxygen sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
A failed engine oil cooler hose can cause engine oil to leak out, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine oil cooler hose melted or burst
oil leaking out of engine while driving
manifold burned a hole through oil cooler hose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
A transmission dip stick leak can cause a fire, which can lead to serious injury or death, as well as significant damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: flames visible through crevices of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed transmission seal can cause a fire, which can lead to serious injury or death, as well as significant damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: flames visible through crevices of the vehicle.
